President Joe Biden spoke at the Huntington Place Convention Center in Detroit, Michigan, addressing the audience at the auto show. He thanked the organizers and introduced various political figures in attendance, including Governor Gretchen Whitmer and Mayor Mike Duggan. The President highlighted his administration's commitment to investing in the American auto industry and transitioning to electric vehicles (EVs). He emphasized the importance of American manufacturing and the role of unions in building the middle class. President Biden announced funding for the construction of electric vehicle charging stations in Michigan and other states, as well as investments in semiconductor manufacturing. He discussed his administration's efforts to create jobs, tackle climate change, and rebuild the country's infrastructure. The President expressed optimism about the future of the auto industry and the ability of American workers to compete globally. He concluded his speech by reaffirming his belief in the potential of the United States and the importance of unity in achieving success.